This paper deals with sentiment analysis, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) and falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also introduces an attention mechanism that considers the cold-start problem, which is a common issue in recommendation systems and falls under the category of information retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also involves machine learning techniques, specifically deep learning, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper deals with user and product information, which is a common topic in social media analysis and falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
